---

When it comes to personalized medicine, choosing the right drug or combination of drugs for the right cancer is of paramount importance. 
The NanoNail is an elegant device that enables us to dose a single tumor with combinations of therapy and evaluate which treatment works best.
I'm thankful to be playing a small role in this project by contributing quantitative spatial analysis of tissue response to these tiny, but informative, drug doses. 
